    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature, boil a little water in a kettle</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-sesame-steak-stir-fry-with-pickled-chilli-and-coriander/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and finely chop the remaining</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> </strong>then peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> into thirds</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-sesame-steak-stir-fry-with-pickled-chilli-and-coriander/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a splash of<strong> boiled water </strong>in a small bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>chilli rounds </strong>to the bowl and set aside to pickle \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled chilli</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>crispy onions </strong>to a small bowl and chop your <strong>coriander </strong>roughly over the top with scissors, stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>coriander crunch</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-sesame-steak-stir-fry-with-pickled-chilli-and-coriander/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> to the plate and coat both sides in the cornflour</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>coated steak</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min or until browned</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-sesame-steak-stir-fry-with-pickled-chilli-and-coriander/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, turn the <strong>steak</strong> and add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>spring onion</strong>, <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> and the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add your <strong>mirin</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min further or until the sauce has started to reduce</p><p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans </strong>under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-sesame-steak-stir-fry-with-pickled-chilli-and-coriander/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the <strong>steak</strong> from the pan and transfer to a clean board</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and add the <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and return to the heat, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-sesame-steak-stir-fry-with-pickled-chilli-and-coriander/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim any fat from the steak and slice thinly</p><p>Return the<strong> sliced steak</strong> to the pan with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong>, then<strong> </strong>stir it all together so that the steak is coated in sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>ginger & sesame steak stir-fry</strong></p><p>Tip: Cook for 1-2 min further if you prefer your steak well done!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-sesame-steak-stir-fry-with-pickled-chilli-and-coriander/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>quick-pickled chilli rounds</strong>, discard the liquid</p><p>Serve the <strong>ginger & sesame steak stir-fry</strong> over the<strong> cooked rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>pickled chilli rounds </strong>and <strong>coriander crunch</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
